102
00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:01.390
If you look at the bottom first, it's very clear to us, all of you who have done

103
00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:05.320
these experiments in the lab yourself or made cells,

104
00:06:05.620 --> 00:06:09.320
cell number increases with the length of ex vivo expansion. Of course.

105
00:06:09.780 --> 00:06:12.220
And it used to be thought that the more cells you infuse, the better.

106
00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:16.060
That is clearly not the case. And in fact, it has become pretty clear that the

107
00:06:16.100 --> 00:06:20.020
per cell potency decreases with the length or

108
00:06:20.080 --> 00:06:22.540
duration of ex vivo manipulation.

109
00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:25.600
And this is supported by some selected preclinical

110
00:06:26.160 --> 00:06:29.580
citations that I have, as well as increasingly from clinical trials, none of which,

