Thanks.

930
00:52:32.852 --> 00:52:33.192
All right.

931
00:52:34.352 --> 00:52:36.092
Fantastic talks so far.

932
00:52:37.372 --> 00:52:41.302
Our next talk is entitled "Precision Targeted Engineering of

933
00:52:41.392 --> 00:52:42.152
CAR T Cells,"

934
00:52:42.992 --> 00:52:45.091
Phil Darcy from Peter McCallum.

935
00:52:47.312 --> 00:52:48.031
Dr. Darcy.

936
00:52:56.572 --> 00:53:00.472
It's an honor to be here, and I'd just like to thank you for the

937
00:53:00.512 --> 00:53:02.392
invitation to present some of our work.

938
00:53:03.072 --> 00:53:06.892
Today, I'm going to talk about our work involving targeted engineering of CAR

939
00:53:06.952 --> 00:53:10.492
T cells by CRISPR editing to

940
00:53:10.532 --> 00:53:13.652
enhance payload delivery, specifically at the tumor site.

941
00:53:16.212 --> 00:53:17.452
These are my disclosures.

942
00:53:22.032 --> 00:53:25.892
So as we've heard so far, engineering T cells with chimeric

943
00:53:25.952 --> 00:53:29.202
antigen receptors is an innovative way to redirect T cells

944
00:53:29.952 --> 00:53:33.692
to cancer cells. And of course, this has shown remarkable effects in

945
00:53:33.752 --> 00:53:37.731
some hematological cancers. However, for solid cancers, this

946
00:53:37.812 --> 00:53:41.272
hasn't been the case, and we've yet to replicate those effects.

947
00:53:41.292 --> 00:53:44.882
And this is due to the suppressive tumor microenvironment,

948
00:53:45.692 --> 00:53:48.932
tumor antigen heterogeneity, and we need to

949
00:53:49.032 --> 00:53:52.732
overcome the lack of trafficking and persistence of the CAR T cells.

950
00:53:53.872 --> 00:53:57.112
We believe one promising approach to do this is through the use of armored CAR T

951
00:53:57.192 --> 00:54:00.832
cells secreting pro-inflammatory cytokines.

952
00:54:05.252 --> 00:54:08.882
So, armored T cells, including CAR T cells, have reached the

953
00:54:08.932 --> 00:54:11.912
clinic. This includes using T cells

954
00:54:12.872 --> 00:54:16.762
expressing IL-12 under the control of an NFAT inducible promoter.

955
00:54:17.212 --> 00:54:20.732
On the left-hand side, you can see in pre-clinical studies,

956
00:54:21.172 --> 00:54:25.092
they've shown inducible iIL-12 expression upon

957
00:54:25.112 --> 00:54:26.832
T cell activation at the tumor site.

958
00:54:27.412 --> 00:54:28.152
Yet in

959
00:54:30.052 --> 00:54:32.072
the clinic, this has resulted in systemic

960
00:54:32.132 --> 00:54:36.080
toxicities.So we believe we

961
00:54:36.120 --> 00:54:39.960
can improve the safety of armored CAR

962
00:54:40.000 --> 00:54:43.700
